tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE charging_stations (
  station_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  station_name VARCHAR(255),
  location_lat DECIMAL,
  location_long DECIMAL,
  power_outlet_type TEXT,
  charging_speed VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE charging_stations (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR,
  location VARCHAR,
  plug_type VARCHAR,
  charge_rate FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE charging_usage (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  station_id INT,
  user_id INT,
  start_time TIMESTAMP,
  end_time TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE charging_station (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  station_name VARCHAR(50),
  location VARCHAR(100),
  city VARCHAR(50),
  country VARCHAR(50),
  charging_capacity INT
);

CREATE TABLE charger (
  charger_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  station_id INT,
  charger_type VARCHAR,
  power_output INT,
  FOREIGN KEY (station_id) REFERENCES charging_station(id)
);

CREATE TABLE charging_session (
  session_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  charger_id INT,
  start_time TIMESTAMP,
  end_time TIMESTAMP,
  energy_delivered DECIMAL,
  FOREIGN KEY (charger_id) REFERENCES charger(charger_id)
);

CREATE TABLE charging_stations (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    station_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    location VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    charging_power INT NOT NULL,
    capacity INT NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE charging_sessions (
    session_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    station_id INT NOT NULL,
    user_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);
